  LLM DSL Bridge Implementation Complete

  New File: /core/services/dsl/llm_dsl_bridge.py

  Key Components:

  1. DOMAIN_RECOGNITION_PROMPT - Comprehensive prompt that instructs GPT-4o-mini to recognize all 13 SKUEL domains:
    - Activity Domains (7): task, habit, goal, event, principle, choice, finance
    - Curriculum Domains (3): ku, ls, lp
    - Meta Domains (3): assignment, report, calendar
    - The Destination (+1): lifepath
  2. DSLTransformResult - Result dataclass with:
    - Original and transformed text
    - Activity counts by domain
    - Processing metadata (model used, tokens, timestamps)
  3. LLMDSLBridgeService - Main service with methods:
    - transform() - Async LLM-powered transformation
    - transform_with_context() - Context-aware transformation (goals, principles)
    - transform_sync() - Rule-based fallback (no API needed)
  4. create_llm_dsl_bridge() - Factory function

  Pipeline Integration

  Natural Journal Text
          ↓
  LLMDSLBridgeService.transform()    ← NEW!
          ↓
  Text with @context() tags
          ↓
  ActivityDSLParser.parse_journal()
          ↓
  ParsedJournal with typed activities
          ↓
  JournalActivityExtractorService.extract_and_create()
          ↓
  SKUEL Entities (Tasks, Habits, Goals, KUs, etc.)

  Example Usage

  from core.services.dsl import create_llm_dsl_bridge

  bridge = create_llm_dsl_bridge()

  result = await bridge.transform(
      text="I need to finish the report by Friday and start exercising daily.",
      user_uid="user:mike",
  )

  # Output:
  # - @context(task) Finish the report @when(Friday) @priority(high)
  # - @context(habit) Exercise @repeat(daily)

